-- 3i Forms Group to Bid for Edinburgh Airport, Times Reports
-- B y   M a t h e w   C a r r
-- 2011-12-18T11:13:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-18/3i-forms-group-to-bid-for-edinburgh-airport-times-reports.html
3i Group Plc (III)  formed a group to bid
for Edinburgh airport, the  Sunday Times reported , citing people
it didn’t identify.  The group includes Universities Superannuation Scheme Ltd.
and  Prudential Plc (PRU) ’s M&G Investment Management Ltd., the
newspaper said. BAA, owned by  Ferrovial SA (FER) , may get more than
500 million pounds ($777 million) for the airport, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mathew Carr in London at 
